name: Ambrosia
description: "Do you need an enthusiastic walking partner who looks like a million dollars on the other end of the leash?  Meet Ambrosia.  After she’s gotten some of her energy out, she enjoys training games that provide mental and physical enrichment.  She’s not a big snuggler — don’t take it personally, but she does enjoy being brushed and massaged when she’s in the right mood.  Because our girl becomes easily overexcited, she has a tendency to overwhelm inexperienced handlers. For this reason, we’re looking for a very dog-savvy adopter with consistency and above average dog-training ability.  Does this sound like you?  Please call us.  Ambrosia needs a real home — she has been patiently waiting for you for way too long."

name: Daisy
description: "Daisy finally found her perfect family almost two years after she was first brought to PIN. She found a home with humans who had experience with active, teachable dogs like her. And she is fitting right in. Her family says, "We absolutely love having her!!""

name: Obie
description: "Obie finally found a home after residing with us for 10 months! He quickly made himself right at home with his new family and is very happy."

name: Larry
description: "Larry came to PIN as a shy and fearful puppy. With the help of our behavior team, Larry gained confidence in noisy and busy environments, learned to play with other dogs, and began to trust humans. He found his home after 6 months with us. His family renamed him to Dexter and absolutely adore him."

name: Donica
prev_location: Humane Society of the North Bay
